<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1186" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1186">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/22.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1605.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your No. 43, of September 29, enclosing a translation of the
                            decree of August 29, 1914, which purports to annul mining titles granted
                            and all acts executed within the mining branch of the Huerta
                            administration during the period from February 19, 1913, to August 15,
                            1914. You request advices from the Department, as to the course it
                            desires your Legation to follow in this matter.</p>
                        <p>In reply I beg to refer you to the Department’s telegram No. 313, of
                            November 4, 4 p.m., already adverted to in the Department’s No. 1602, of
                            November 18.</p>
                        <p>Thanking you for your prompt action in the matter,</p>
                        <p>I avail [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>